ropeable
Homonym Number:
Word Class: adjective
Sense Number:
Definition:violently angry, needing restraint, fit to be tied spg also ropable


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: *OED online: Austral & NZ Slang.  *ca1945 Victoria Univ. College undergraduates; cf also punning corruption rapeable (of a girl).
